The paper deals with the problem of alpha matting, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) that involves estimating the opacity of an object in an image or video. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques (cs.AI) and the processing of images and videos (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method using benchmark metrics (cs.LG) and the use of graphics (cs.GR) to illustrate the results.
